SUMMARY:Model Mondays - Open Models with Fireworks AI & Microsoft Foundry 
 Tools
DESCRIPTION:Microsoft Reactor Toronto\nPartner Spotlight - Running Open Mo
 dels at Scale: Fireworks AI on Microsoft Foundry\nChoosing a model is easy
 . Scaling it reliably is the hard part. In this Model Mondays session\, jo
 in **Shaunak Godbole**\, Field CTO at Fireworks AI\, for interactive demos
  and a deeper look at how developers can run best‑in‑class open models
  at scale without managing infrastructure\, including bringing the models 
 they already trust through bring‑your‑own‑weights with Fireworks on 
 Microsoft Foundry.\n\nTech Spotlight - Microsoft Foundry Tools & MCP\nThe 
 Foundry Tools provide a central hub for agents to discover and integrate t
 ools (MCP Servers) to extend their capabilities. Join **SeokJin Han** as h
 e demonstrates Foundry Tools and the Model Context Protocol integration. L
 earn how agents can discover and utilize tools through MCP Servers\, exten
 ding their capabilities with a standardized interface and growing ecosyste
 m.\n\n----------------------------------------------\n[Explore the repo](h
 ttps://github.com/microsoft/model-mondays/blob/main/docs/model-mondays/202
 6-03-23-s03-e14.md)\n\n📢 [Join the conversation on Discord!](https://ak
 a.ms/model-mondays/discord)\n\n📌 This session is a part of the Model Mo
 ndays series. [Learn more here!](https://developer.microsoft.com/reactor/s
 eries/S-1485/?wt.mc_id=meetup_S-1485_webpage_reactor)
URL;VALUE=URI:https://www.meetup.com/microsoft-reactor-toronto/events/3133
 33526/
